BST1.description: Supply input for high-side MOSFET gate drive circuit. Connect a ceramic capacitor between BSTx and SWx pins. An internal diode is connected between V5D and BSTx. (DAP pin: 19). Quiescent current I_Q(xBST): 200uA min, 250uA typ, 300uA max. Bootstrap UVLO V_BSTx(UV) falling: 2.60V min, 2.95V typ, 3.30V max; Hysteresis: 120mV min, 184mV typ, 250mV max.
BST1.name: BST1

BST2.description: Supply input for high-side MOSFET gate drive circuit. Connect a ceramic capacitor between BSTx and SWx pins. An internal diode is connected between V5D and BSTx. (DAP pin: 30). Quiescent current I_Q(xBST): 200uA min, 250uA typ, 300uA max. Bootstrap UVLO V_BSTx(UV) falling: 2.60V min, 2.95V typ, 3.30V max; Hysteresis: 120mV min, 184mV typ, 250mV max.
BST2.name: BST2

COMP1.description: Output of internal transconductance error amplifier. Connect an integral compensation network to ensure stability. (DAP pin: 16). Abs Max Voltage: -0.3V to 5.5V. Transconductance g_M: 450 uA/V typ. Source/Sink Current I_COMPx: 45 uA typ. Leakage I_COMPx(LKG): 2.5 nA max. Startup Threshold V_COMPx(ST): 2.45V typ (rising). Over-Voltage Threshold V_COMPx(OV): 3.0V min, 3.2V typ (rising).
COMP1.name: COMP1

COMP2.description: Output of internal transconductance error amplifier. Connect an integral compensation network to ensure stability. (DAP pin: 1). Abs Max Voltage: -0.3V to 5.5V. Transconductance g_M: 450 uA/V typ. Source/Sink Current I_COMPx: 45 uA typ. Leakage I_COMPx(LKG): 2.5 nA max. Startup Threshold V_COMPx(ST): 2.45V typ (rising). Over-Voltage Threshold V_COMPx(OV): 3.0V min, 3.2V typ (rising).
COMP2.name: COMP2

CSN1.description: Negative input (–) of internal rail-to-rail transconductance error amplifier. Connect directly to the negative node of the LED current sense resistor, Rcs. (DAP pin: 17). Abs Max Voltage to GND: -0.5V to 65V. Abs Max Current (GND to CSNx, <10us): 430mA. Common mode range: 0V to (VINx - 0.5V).
CSN1.name: CSN1

CSN2.description: Negative input (–) of internal rail-to-rail transconductance error amplifier. Connect directly to the negative node of the LED current sense resistor, Rcs. (DAP pin: 32). Abs Max Voltage to GND: -0.5V to 65V. Abs Max Current (GND to CSNx, <10us): 430mA. Common mode range: 0V to (VINx - 0.5V).
CSN2.name: CSN2

CSP1.description: Positive input (+) of internal rail-to-rail transconductance error amplifier. Connect directly to the positive node of the LED current sense resistor, Rcs. (DAP pin: 18). Abs Max Voltage to GND: -0.5V to 65V. Abs Max Voltage (CSPx to CSNx): -0.5V to 0.5V. Abs Max Current (GND to CSPx, <10us): 430mA. Output short circuit detection V_CSPx(SHT) rising: 2.65V typ. Recommended Slew Rate dv/dt_CSP: 5 V/us max.
CSP1.name: CSP1

CSP2.description: Positive input (+) of internal rail-to-rail transconductance error amplifier. Connect directly to the positive node of the LED current sense resistor, Rcs. (DAP pin: 31). Abs Max Voltage to GND: -0.5V to 65V. Abs Max Voltage (CSPx to CSNx): -0.5V to 0.5V. Abs Max Current (GND to CSPx, <10us): 430mA. Output short circuit detection V_CSPx(SHT) rising: 2.65V typ. Recommended Slew Rate dv/dt_CSP: 5 V/us max.
CSP2.name: CSP2

FLT.description: Open-drain fault indicator. Connect to V5D with a resistor to create an active low fault signal output. (DAP pin: 22).
FLT.name: FLT

GND.description: Signal ground. Return for the internal voltage reference and analog circuits. Connect to circuit ground to complete return path. (DAP pins: [7, 10])
GND.name: GND

LHI.description: Limp-home and standalone mode LED current reference set point. The voltage can be used instead of SPI registers to set LED current. The operation is configured through the LHCFG1 register. Setting voltage below 148 mV disables both channels and setting the voltage above 200 mV enables both channels. (DAP pin: 23). Abs Max Voltage: -0.3V to 5.5V. Source current I_LHI: 8uA min, 10uA typ, 12uA max. Shutdown threshold V_LHI(SD) rising: 174mV min, 200mV typ, 227mV max; falling: 119mV min, 148mV typ, 176mV max.
LHI.name: LHI

MISO.description: Open-drain SPI slave data output. Connect a 4.7-kΩ resistor to V5D digital supply voltage. (DAP pin: 26). R_DS-MISO: 50 Ohm typ (at 10mA).
MISO.name: MISO

PGND.description: Ground returns for low-side MOSFETs. (DAP pins: [3, 4, 13, 14])
PGND.name: PGND

SW1.description: Switching output of the regulator. Internally connected to both power MOSFETs. Connect to the power inductor. (DAP pins: [20, 21])
SW1.name: SW1

SW2.description: Switching output of the regulator. Internally connected to both power MOSFETs. Connect to the power inductor. (DAP pins: [28, 29])
SW2.name: SW2

UDIM1.description: Undervoltage lockout and external PWM dimming input. Connect to VIN through a resistor divider to implement input undervoltage protection. Diode couple external PWM signal to enable dimming. Do not float. (DAP pin: 15). UDIM source current (UVLO hysteresis) I_UDIMx(UVLO): 8uA min, 10uA typ, 12uA max.
UDIM1.name: UDIM1

UDIM2.description: Undervoltage lockout and external PWM dimming input. Connect to VIN through a resistor divider to implement input undervoltage protection. Diode couple external PWM signal to enable dimming. Do not float. (DAP pin: 2). UDIM source current (UVLO hysteresis) I_UDIMx(UVLO): 8uA min, 10uA typ, 12uA max.
UDIM2.name: UDIM2

V5A.description: Analog supply voltage. Locally decouple to GND using a 100-nF to 1-µF ceramic capacitor located close to the controller. (DAP pin: 8). UVLO V_V5D,A(UVLO) rising: 4.10V typ, 4.26V max; falling: 3.84V min, 4.00V typ. Standby current I_V5A(STBY): 4mA typ, 5mA max. Sleep current I_V5A(SLEEP): 16nA typ, 300nA max.
V5A.name: V5A

V5D.description: Digital supply voltage. Locally decouple to GND using a 2.2-µF to 4.7-µF ceramic capacitor located close to the controller. (DAP pin: 9). UVLO V_V5D,A(UVLO) rising: 4.10V typ, 4.26V max; falling: 3.84V min, 4.00V typ. Standby current I_V5D(STBY): 0.9mA typ, 1.3mA max. Sleep current I_V5D(SLEEP): 17uA typ, 24uA max. Switching current I_V5D(SW): 12mA typ, 20mA max (f_SW=1MHz).
V5D.name: V5D

VIN1.description: Power inputs and connections to high-side MOSFET drain node. Connect to the power supply and bypass capacitors CIN. The path from the VIN pin to high frequency bypass CIN and PGND must be as short as possible. (DAP pins: [11, 12]). Sleep current I_VINx(SLEEP): 2uA typ, 4uA max (VINx=15V).
VIN1.name: VIN1

VIN2.description: Power inputs and connections to high-side MOSFET drain node. Connect to the power supply and bypass capacitors CIN. The path from the VIN pin to high frequency bypass CIN and PGND must be as short as possible. (DAP pins: [5, 6]). Sleep current I_VINx(SLEEP): 2uA typ, 4uA max (VINx=15V).
VIN2.name: VIN2

fields.description: Reset open-drain fault output if there are no active faults in the system. Note that this bit is write-only. Any reads of this register return 0 in the FPINRST bit location. 0 = Do not care, 1 = Reset open-drain fault output.
fields.name: FPINRST

fields.description: PWM phase shift setting for internal PWM generator.

digital_physical_map.0: 180° phase shift between internally generated PWM signals
digital_physical_map.1: 0° phase shift between internally generated PWM signals

fields.name: PWMPH

fields.description: Software limp-home mode. The limp-home mode can be activated by writing to the register. The bit is also set high in case of communication failure. The bit has to be written to zero to return to normal operation.

digital_physical_map.0: Normal Operation
digital_physical_map.1: Operation in limp-home state

fields.name: LHSW

fields.description: Communication watch dog timer enable.

digital_physical_map.0: Disable communication watch dog timer
digital_physical_map.1: Enable communication watch dog timer

fields.name: CMWEN

fields.description: This bit is used to enable internal PWM generator function for channel 2.

digital_physical_map.0: LED current duty cycle of channel 2 controlled by the external signal connected to UDIM2 input
digital_physical_map.1: LED current duty cycle of channel 2 controlled by the internal PWM generator (registers PWMDIV and CH2PWM). UDIM2 input must be above V_UDIM2(UVLO).

fields.name: CH2INTPWM

fields.description: CH2 enable. This bit controls the operation of channel 2.

digital_physical_map.0: Disable LED channel 2
digital_physical_map.1: Enable LED channel 2

fields.name: CH2EN

fields.description: This bit is used to enable internal PWM generator function for channel 1.

digital_physical_map.0: LED current duty cycle of channel 1 controlled by external signal connected to UDIM1 input
digital_physical_map.1: LED current duty cycle of channel 1 controlled by internal PWM generator (registers PWMDIV and CH1PWM). UDIM1 input must be above V_UDIM1(UVLO).

fields.name: CH1INTPWM

fields.description: CH1 enable. This bit controls the operation of channel 1.

digital_physical_map.0: Disable LED channel 1
digital_physical_map.1: Enable LED channel 1

fields.name: CH1EN

fields.description: IFT sets the counter limit for the fault timer.

digital_physical_map.0: 3.6 ms fault timer
digital_physical_map.1: 7.2 ms fault timer

fields.name: IFT

fields.description: Channel 2 thermal shutdown fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 2 auto-restarts based on internal temperature hysteresis.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 2 is latched off; CH2EN bit is reset and channel 2 is disabled until the CH2EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH2TSFL

fields.description: Channel 2 high-side FET current limit fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 2 auto-restarts after the ILIM fault timer has expired.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 2 is latched off; CH2EN bit is reset and channel 2 is disabled until the CH2EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH2HSILIMFL

fields.description: Channel 2 low-side FET current limit fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 2 auto-restarts after the ILIM fault timer has expired.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 2 is latched off; CH2EN bit is reset and channel 2 is disabled until the CH2EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH2LSILIMFL

fields.description: Channel 1 thermal shutdown fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 1 auto-restarts based on internal temperature hysteresis.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 1 is latched off; CH1EN bit is reset and channel 1 is disabled until the CH1EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH1TSFL

fields.description: Channel 1 high side FET current limit fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 1 auto-restarts after the ILIM fault timer has expired.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 1 is latched off; CH1EN bit is reset and channel 1 is disabled until the CH1EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH1HSILIMFL

fields.description: Channel 1 low side FET current limit fault response.

digital_physical_map.0: Channel 1 auto-restarts after the ILIM fault timer has expired.
digital_physical_map.1: Channel 1 is latched off; CH1EN bit is reset and channel 1 is disabled until the CH1EN bit is programmed high by SPI command.

fields.name: CH1LSILIMFL

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x02_7_4

digital_physical_map.0: Tap point set to bit 16 corresponding to 6.1 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.1: Tap point set to bit 17 corresponding to 12.1 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.10: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.11: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.12: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.13: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.14: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.15: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.2: Tap point set to bit 18 corresponding to 24.3 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.3: Tap point set to bit 19 corresponding to 48.5 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.4: Tap point set to bit 20 corresponding to 97.1 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.5: Tap point set to bit 21 corresponding to 194.2 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.6: Tap point set to bit 22 corresponding to 388.3 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.7: Tap point set to bit 23 corresponding to 776.7 ms (typical) watch dog period.
digital_physical_map.8: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.
digital_physical_map.9: Tap point set to bit 24 corresponding to 1.52 s (typical) watchdog period.

fields.name: CMWTAP

fields.description: Indicates low-side switch current limit fault on channel 2. Low-side switch current is greater than 1.5 A (typical).
fields.name: CH2LSILIM

fields.description: Indicates high-side switch current limit fault on channel 2. High-side switch current is greater than 2.7 A (typical).
fields.name: CH2HSILIM

fields.description: Indicates output short circuit fault on channel 2. CSP pin voltage is below 2.45 V.
fields.name: CH2SHORT

fields.description: Indicates overvoltage condition on COMP2 pin. COMP2 pin voltage is greater than 3.2 V.
fields.name: CH2COMPOV

fields.description: Indicates low-side switch current limit fault on channel 1. Low-side switch current is greater than 1.5 A (typical).
fields.name: CH1LSILIM

fields.description: Indicates high-side switch current limit fault on channel 1. High-side switch current is greater than 2.7 A (typical).
fields.name: CH1HSILIM

fields.description: Indicates output short circuit fault on channel 1. CSP pin voltage is below 2.45 V.
fields.name: CH1SHORT

fields.description: Indicates overvoltage condition on COMP1 pin. COMP1 pin voltage is greater than 3.2 V.
fields.name: CH1COMPOV

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x04_7_6

fields.description: Indicates overtemperature thermal protection for channel 2. The channel automatically restarts when the bit is cleared to 0.
fields.name: CH2TP

fields.description: Indicates bootstrap undervoltage fault condition on channel 2. BST2 pin voltage is less than 2.95 V.
fields.name: CH2BSTUV

fields.description: Indicates channel 2 operation at maximum duty cycle.
fields.name: CH2TOFFMIN

fields.description: Indicates overtemperature thermal protection for channel 1. The channel automatically restarts when the bit is cleared to 0.
fields.name: CH1TP

fields.description: Indicates bootstrap undervoltage fault condition on channel 1. BST1 pin voltage is less than 2.95 V.
fields.name: CH1BSTUV

fields.description: Indicates channel 1 operation at maximum duty cycle.
fields.name: CH1TOFFMIN

fields.description: Indicates standalone mode. This bit can be cleared by issuing the RESET or DETECT command.
fields.name: STANDALONE

fields.description: Indicates V5A undervoltage fault condition.
fields.name: V5AUV

fields.description: Indicates the number of times the communication watchdog timer has expired.

digital_physical_map.0: Default (normal operation)
digital_physical_map.1: Watchdog has expired 1 time.
digital_physical_map.3: Watchdog has expired 3 times. Device transitions into limp-home mode.

fields.name: CMWTO

fields.description: Indicates overtemperature thermal warning.
fields.name: TW

fields.description: Power cycle bit is set at power up and is considered a fault. The PC bit must be cleared before the channels can be enabled.
fields.name: PC

fields.description: Logic OR of the fault bits for channel 2 excluding over temperature thermal warning.
fields.name: CH2STATUS

fields.description: Logic OR of the fault bits for channel 1 excluding over temperature thermal warning.
fields.name: CH1STATUS

fields.description: Sets the Thermal Warning (TW) bit when the most significant 8 bits of the ADC reading of the TEMP value (TEMP[9:2]) exceed the programmed value. Implicit TEMP[1:0] are 0 for this comparison. Default 0x8A (138) corresponds to 125°C. Actual temperature calculation: T_J_warning = 0.7168 * (TWLMT_value * 4) - 271.51 °C.
fields.name: TWLMT

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x07_7_2

fields.description: Device sleep mode. The low-power sleep mode can be activated by writing to the register.

digital_physical_map.0: Exit sleep mode and return to normal operation (SLEEP OFF).
digital_physical_map.1: Enter sleep mode (SLEEP ON).

fields.name: SLEEP

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x08_7_2

fields.description: Channel 1 analog current control (10-bit). Sets the reference for LED current regulation. I_LED = (V_DAC(FS) * CH1IADJ[9:0]) / (1024 * 14 * R_CS). V_DAC(FS) typ 2.45V.

digital_physical_map.-1: I_LED = (2.45 * VALUE) / (14336 * R_CS) A, where VALUE is the 10-bit CH1IADJ value and R_CS is in Ohms.

fields.name: CH1IADJ

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x0A_7_2

fields.description: Channel 2 analog current control (10-bit). Sets the reference for LED current regulation. I_LED = (V_DAC(FS) * CH2IADJ[9:0]) / (1024 * 14 * R_CS). V_DAC(FS) typ 2.45V.

digital_physical_map.-1: I_LED = (2.45 * VALUE) / (14336 * R_CS) A, where VALUE is the 10-bit CH2IADJ value and R_CS is in Ohms.

fields.name: CH2IADJ

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x0C_7_3

fields.description: This 3-bit value selects the clock divider for the internal PWM generator. The PWM clock is derived based on typical oscillator frequency of 10.8 MHz. PWM_FREQ = (10.8 MHz / Div_Factor) / 1024.

digital_physical_map.0: Divide oscillator clock by 7 (f_PWM = 1507 Hz)
digital_physical_map.1: Divide oscillator clock by 8 (f_PWM = 1318 Hz)

fields.name: PWMDIV

fields.description: Channel 1 PWM width control (10-bit). Sets the duty cycle for the internal PWM generator for channel 1. Duty Cycle = CH1PWM / 1024.
fields.name: CH1PWM

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x0E_7_2

fields.description: Channel 2 PWM width control (10-bit). Sets the duty cycle for the internal PWM generator for channel 2. Duty Cycle = CH2PWM / 1024.
fields.name: CH2PWM

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x10_7_2

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x11_7_6

fields.description: Channel 1 on-time control (6-bit). The pseudo-fixed switching frequency for channel 1 is set by writing to this register. Default value (7) is set to ensure 437-kHz switching frequency. See Table 8-1 for mappings. Theoretical f_SW = (CH1TON[5:0] + 1) / (4e-8 * (CH1TON[5:0] + 1) + 18e-6) Hz.
fields.name: CH1TON

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x12_7_6

fields.description: Channel 2 on-time control (6-bit). The pseudo-fixed switching frequency for channel 2 is set by writing to this register. Default value (7) is set to ensure 437-kHz switching frequency. See Table 8-1 for mappings. Theoretical f_SW = (CH2TON[5:0] + 1) / (4e-8 * (CH2TON[5:0] + 1) + 18e-6) Hz.
fields.name: CH2TON

fields.description: ADC measurement of the drain voltage node for channel 1 (VIN1). The VIN1 pin voltage is internally attenuated by 0.037. Conversion ratio: 65V / 255 counts. VIN1_voltage = CH1VIN_ADC_value * (65/255) V.

digital_physical_map.-1: VIN1_voltage = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH1VIN_ADC

fields.description: ADC measurement of the CSN1 node for channel 1. The CSN1 pin voltage is internally attenuated by 0.037. Conversion ratio: 65V / 255 counts. CSN1_voltage = CH1VLED_ADC_value * (65/255) V.

digital_physical_map.-1: CSN1_voltage = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH1VLED_ADC

fields.description: ADC measurement of the CSN1 node for channel 1 before falling edge of PWM signal. Same conversion as CH1VLED_ADC.

digital_physical_map.-1: CSN1_voltage_ON = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH1VLEDON_ADC

fields.description: ADC measurement of the CSN1 node for channel 1 before rising edge of PWM signal. Same conversion as CH1VLED_ADC.

digital_physical_map.-1: CSN1_voltage_OFF = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH1VLEDOFF_ADC

digital_physical_map.-1: VIN2_voltage = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH2VIN_ADC

fields.name: CH2VLED_ADC

fields.description: ADC measurement of the CSN2 node for channel 2 before falling edge of PWM signal. Same conversion as CH2VLED_ADC.

digital_physical_map.-1: CSN2_voltage_ON = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: CH2VLEDON_ADC

fields.description: ADC measurement of the CSN2 node for channel 2 before rising edge of PWM signal. Same conversion as CH2VLED_ADC.

digital_physical_map.-1: CSN2_voltage_OFF = VALUE * 0.2549 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.description: ADC measurement of the junction temperature (10-bit). Equation: T_J = 0.7168 * TEMP_ADC_value - 271.51 °C.

digital_physical_map.-1: V5D_voltage = VALUE * 0.0209 V, where VALUE is the 8-bit register value.

fields.name: LHI_ADC

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x22_7_2

fields.description: Filtered ADC measurement of LHI input (10-bit). This register is only updated when LHIFILTH is read. LHIFILTH must always be read first. Same conversion as LHI_ADC.

digital_physical_map.-1: LHIFILT_voltage = VALUE * 0.002395 V, where VALUE is the 10-bit LHIFILT_ADC value.

fields.name: LHIFILT_ADC

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x24_7_2

fields.description: Channel 1 analog current control in limp-home mode (10-bit). Same conversion as CH1IADJ.

digital_physical_map.-1: I_LED = (2.45 * VALUE) / (14336 * R_CS) A, where VALUE is the 10-bit LH1IADJ value and R_CS is in Ohms.

fields.name: LH1IADJ

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x26_7_2

fields.description: Channel 2 analog current control in limp-home mode (10-bit). Same conversion as CH2IADJ.

digital_physical_map.-1: I_LED = (2.45 * VALUE) / (14336 * R_CS) A, where VALUE is the 10-bit LH2IADJ value and R_CS is in Ohms.

fields.name: LH2IADJ

fields.description: Channel 1 PWM width control in limp-home mode (10-bit). Duty Cycle = LH1PWM / 1024.
fields.name: LH1PWM

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x29_7_2

fields.description: Channel 2 PWM width control in limp-home mode (10-bit). Duty Cycle = LH2PWM / 1024.
fields.name: LH2PWM

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x2B_7_2

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x2C_7_6

fields.description: Channel 1 on-time control in limp-home mode (6-bit). Same mapping as CH1TON.
fields.name: LH1TON

fields.description: Reserved bits.
fields.name: RESERVED_0x2D_7_6

fields.description: Channel 2 on-time control in limp-home mode (6-bit). Same mapping as CH2TON.
fields.name: LH2TON

fields.description: Write 0xC3 to reset all writable registers to default values and return channel enable state machines to LOAD state (watchdog disabled). Write 0xD4 to reset all writable registers to default values and return channel enable state machines to DETECT state (watchdog enabled, after clearing CMWTO bits in STATUS3). This register is write-only.
fields.name: RESET_CMD
